  "original_title": "\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dc3\u0dca,\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca,\u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0da7\u0db1\u0da7;\u0dc3\u0da2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf \u0db1\u0ddc\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dallas, Ranil, Anura Kumara in the presidential battle; Sajith will not nominate",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The names of three members of parliament for the next presidential battle of the country, which all Sri Lankans are waiting for with great interest, were approved today (July 19) when the parliament met.",
        "During the 10-minute parliamentary session, opposition leader Sajith Premadasa proposed the name of Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna MP and former minister Dallas Alahaperuma for the post of President, and Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Chairman G. L. Peirce seconded the motion.",
        "The Leader of the Parliament, Minister Dinesh Gunawardena proposed the name of Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe and it was confirmed by Samagi Jana Balawega MP Manusha Nanayakkara.",
        "National People's Force MP Vijitha Herath proposed the name of the party's leader Anura Kumara Dissanayake and MP Harini Amarasuriya seconded the proposal.",
        "Meanwhile, the General Secretary of the Parliament said that the voting will be held on Wednesday, July 20, as the names of more than one MP have been proposed for the post of President.",
        "Parliament was accordingly adjourned until 10 am on Wednesday, July 20.",
        "Before the start of the parliamentary session, opposition leader Sajith Premadasa said in a tweet, \"For the good of my beloved country and the people I love, I am withdrawing my presidential candidacy. Samagi Jana Balawegaya, our alliance and our opposition partners will work hard to win Dallas Alahaperuma.\" doing.\" Namely."
      ],
